OL,3,CAlmost half of people dipping into
OL,4,Ctheir savings to cover everyday costs
OL,6,FOverall, people are having to dip into
OL,7,Ftheir savings around three times per
OL,8,Fmonth on average, while 27% say they
OL,9,Fare unable to save anything at all and
OL,10,F25% can save only between #100 and
OL,11,F#250 each month.
OL,13,FSome 20% only managed to make the
OL,14,Fminimum repayment on their most recent
OL,15,Fcredit card bill and less than half
OL,16,F(48%) are regularly paying off their
OL,17,Fcredit card balance in full each month.
