OL,3,CAlmost half of people dipping into
OL,4,Ctheir savings to cover everyday costs
OL,6,F"However, our research shows that many
OL,7,Fpeople are still struggling to save on
OL,8,Fa monthly basis, and a significant
OL,9,Fnumber are having to rely on those
OL,10,Fsavings each month to pay for everyday
OL,11,Fbills or lean on credit cards for
OL,12,Fadditional costs such as holidays."
OL,14,F"Credit cards can be a valuable tool
OL,15,Ffor making purchases, such a paying
OL,16,Ffor holidays. However, when taking out
OL,17,Fa credit card you have to be mindful
OL,18,Fof not borrowing more than you can
OL,19,Fafford. It's worthwhile paying off
OL,20,Fyour credit card balance in full every
OL,21,Fmonth to avoid paying interest."
